displaytitle: On Toward Washington: One of 29 mule carts that pulled out of Marks, Mississippi, on a leg of the Poor People's trek to the nation's capital moves across the flatlands of Mississippi as sundown approaches Monday. The wagon train segment of the Southern Christian Leadership Conference's latest Civil Rights drive was to have departed last week, but was delayed because mules being used did not have proper shoes for walking on concrete
creditline: Gift of M. Robin Krasny, Class of 1973
inscribed: With typewritten title and date on recto; with date stamp on verso
